'''Inşirah Hanım''' ({{lang-ota|انشراح خانم}}; 10 July 1887 &ndash; 10 June 1930) was the second wife of Sultan [[Mehmed VI]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]].{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}

==Early life==
Inşirah Hanım was born on 10 July 1887{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}} in Maşukiye, [[İzmit]]. Born as Seniye Voçibe, she was a member of [[Ubykh people|Ubykh]] noble family, Voçibe. Her father was Aziz Bey Voçibe. She had an elder brother named Zeki Bey (1885 – 1932). She was the paternal neice of [[Dürrüaden Kadın]], wife of Sultan [[Mehmed V]].{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=188, n. 88}}

She was taken into palace by her aunt Dürrüaden. At the age of sixteen, she became a lady-in-waiting to [[Şayeste Hanım]], wife of Sultan [[Abdulmejid I]]. She was tall, had slender figure, long chestnut hair, and faint blue eyes. She was interested in painting.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=188}}

==Marriage==
One day, when Mehmed was in his forties, he visited his adoptive mother Şayeste Hanım at her palace. Here he saw Inşirah, then seventeen years old, and fell in love with her. He asked Şayeste to give him Inşirah in marriage.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=70}} Inşirah refused to this proposal. However, at her brother's insistence, she agreed. The marriage took place on 8 July 1905{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=188-9}} in the Çengelköy Palace.{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=706}} No issue came of this marriage.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=70}} After her marrige, her brother, Zeki Bey became aide-de-camp to Mehmed.{{sfn|Bardakçı|2017|p=87}}

Inşirah was said to be a jealous lady. One day, she caught Mehmed in the bedroom with a servant girl named Periru. She immediately abandoned him, and went back to her family.{{sfn|Açba|2004|p=71-2}} Mehmed divorced her on 17 November 1909.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=189}}{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=706}}

==Later years and death==
After her divorce, she moved in her aunt's Validebağı Palace. When the imperial family went into exile in 1924, she went to Cairo.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=189}} Her brother remained with Mehmed, even after her divorce, and followed him into exile.{{sfn|Bardakçı|2017|p=87}}

Inşirah committed suicide on 10 June 1930,{{sfn|Uluçay|2011|p=263}}{{sfn|Sakaoğlu|2008|p=706}} by tossing herself into the river [[Nile]]. Her body was brought to Istanbul by the Naaşi family. She was buried in Eyüp Sultan Cemetery.{{sfn|Açba|2007|p=190}}

