{{orphan|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Ngando Pickett | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = Yaoundé | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = {{flag|Cameroon}} | other_names = Henry Mouyebe | known_for = Football mascot | occupation = }}
Henry Mouyebe, better known as '''Ngando Pickett''' is a high-profile [[Cameroon]]ian [[association football|football]] fan.<ref name="cameroonwebnews">{{cite web|url=http://cameroonwebnews.com/sports/meeting-cameroons-super-fan/|title=Meeting Cameroon’s super fan |last=Nayar|first=Anjali|date=24 May 2010|publisher=CameroonWebNews.com|accessdate=25 May 2010}}</ref> He is recognisable at Cameroon national football games for his painted body and musical displays.
His friends named him after [[Wilson Pickett]] as he was an accomplished dancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://peuplesawa.com/fr/bnnews.php?nid=200&kat=3&vip=0|title=Interview|date=12 February 2006|publisher=peuplesawa.com|accessdate=25 May 2010}}</ref>
In May 2010, sports manufacturer [[Puma SE]] used his image in a high-profile advertising campaign without his permission. Pickett is now contemplating legal action against Puma.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journalducameroun.com/article.php?aid=5166|title=Journal Du Cameroun.com: Le Camerounais Ngando Picket menace de poursuivre l'équipementier Puma|date=7 May 2010|publisher=journalducameroun.com|accessdate=25 May 2010}}</ref> Speaking of the incident he said "I am extremely embarrassed as my image is everywhere, I have rights to my image on my person. I have nothing with Puma. Puma has no right to use my picture."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cameroun-online.com/actualite,actu-14084.html|title=Ngando Pickett rêve de fortune|date=May 11, 2010|publisher=Cameroun Online|accessdate=25 May 2010}}</ref>
